description: The duo, captured on video in a County Donegal garden, are not exactly birds of a feather.
title: Bird watching: The robin that thinks a cuckoo is its baby
title_page: Bird watching: The robin that thinks a cuckoo is its baby - BBC News
maintext: "The young cuckoo hatches after only 12 days and quickly pushes the hosts' eggs or babies out of the nest. After 19 days it leaves the nest, but the hosts continue to feed it for two more weeks, by which time it has grown much bigger than them."
